Murder-accused teenager Heather Mack has been keeping her baby with her in a crowded cell in Bali 's Kerobokan prison .
Mack , from Chicago , could spend 15 years in jail for the murder of her mother , 62-year-old socialite Sheila von Wiese-Mack , whose body was stuffed inside a suitcase .
Yasona Laoly , Indonesia 's Justice and Human Rights Minister has offered Mack the chance to place the baby with a family to care for the child .